On a flatspace-rendered site, extractArticle slices only <body> content and STRIPS <head><style>, <header>, <footer>. Any fix-bearing CSS for injected article content (e.g. Chart.js canvas sizing) must live in the renderer's render-mode shipping <style> targeting the injected article host element, NOT in the source page's <head>. Witness the placement by grepping the BUILT dist artifact for the rule (head-placed rules show 0 matches). Chart.js with responsive:true+maintainAspectRatio:false grows unbounded unless its canvas box is CSS-determined with height/max-height !important. Verify the fix by measuring canvas getBoundingClientRect across two browser reads seconds apart -- stable height witnesses it, eyeballing does not.